        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 4:13PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Powellsville, or 9 miles south of Ahoskie, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Powellsville around 420 PM EDT.
Ahoskie around 425 PM EDT.
Cofield around 440 PM EDT.
Winton around 445 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Whites Crossroads,
Tunis, Earleys, Menola, Trap, Union, Wakelon, Askewville, Oak Villa,
and Saint John.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
